{{- define "content" }}
<p class="lead">
    Titles are important, <u>bad titles make it hard to dupe check future uploads</u>.<br>
    <span class="text-primary-emphasis">Keep titles simple, concise and clean.</span>
</p>
<div>
    <p class="lead">Bad examples:</p>
    <ol class="list-numbered">
        <li><q>Microsoft Visual Studio for WinNT V1.1001.1</q></li>
        <li><q>INC cracktro for EA's Sim City 2000!</q></li>
        <li><q>Zool 2 by Virgin Interactive +16 MEGA trainer</q></li>
        <li><q>Microsoft Windows 95 4.00.950 *STORE RELEASE FINAL*</q></li>
        <li><q>EA NFL 98 100% BYTE PATCHED AND WORKING</q></li>
    </ol>
    <p class="lead">Good examples:</p>
    <ol class="list-numbered">
        <li><q>Visual Studio v1.1</q></li>
        <li><q>Sim City 2000</q></li>
        <li><q>Zool 2</q></li>
        <li><q>Windows 95</q></li>
        <li><q>NFL 98 fix</q></li>
    </ol>
</div>
<hr class="ms-1 w-25">
<div class="lead">
    <ul class="list-unstyled">
        <li>Don't use ALL CAPS, copy.pasted.directory.names, 1337 text, or filenames.</li>
        <li>List the <strong>name</strong> of the game or application <strong>before</strong> any supplementary info.</li>
    </ul>
    <ul class="list-unstyled">
        <li>Do not include the publisher as these can attract DMCA take downs when shown on search engines.<br><small class="text-body-secondary">Exceptions for generic named products, ie: <q>Norton Backup</q> <q>Atari Football</q>.</small></li>
        <li>Use the prefix <q>fix</q> when needed.<br><small class="text-body-secondary">But avoid too specific terms like <q>cracked</q>, <q>patched</q>, <q>bytecrack</q>, <q>hack</q>, etc.</small></li>
        <li>Don't include unnecessary information.<br><small class="text-body-secondary">Semantic software versions, build numbers; or release justifications, <q>100% final</q>, <q>US release</q>, <q>multilanguage</q>, etc.</small></li>
        <li>Don't include redundant information.<br><small class="text-body-secondary">Words such as <q>trainer</q>, <q>installer</q>, <q>cracktro</q>, <q>keymaker</q>, <q>serial generator</q>, using the group name, etc.</small></li>
    </ul>
    <ul class="list-unstyled">
        <li>Only ignore the above when it is required for the clarity of the artefact.</li>
        <li>It's fine to have an empty title if the other artefact metadata or screenshot provides enough information.
            <br><small class="text-body-secondary">Text and image art, courier group NFOs, BBS ads, etc., often don't need a title.</small>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
{{- end}}